item.description:
In part one we setup a project in Azure Devops, create an Azure repo, added an ARM template to the repo and created a build pipeline. In this post we&rsquo;ll create a release pipeline to actually deploy our resources in Azure.
Within Azure Devops open our project and select &lsquo;Releases&rsquo; and select &lsquo;New Pipeline&rsquo;
On the next page choose under select template choose &lsquo;Start with an empty job&rsquo;
By default the stage is called Stage 1 as per the above screenshot, I&rsquo;ve renamed mine to Deployment
